      "case_id": "tier1_clean_general_track_packet",
      "title": "Clean general five-year packet",
      "narrative": "The packet includes a permanent resident card, N-400 intake summary, travel table, English/civics results, oath worksheet, FBI criminal history check, court docket search, and USCIS interview worksheet. The applicant is 37 years old and has been an LPR for 6 years. The travel table lists one 21-day trip and no other travel. Physical presence worksheet states 41 months present in the United States during the five-year period. Residence worksheet states 9 months in the same USCIS district. English test passed, civics test passed, applicant is willing to take the oath, and the oath worksheet states attachment to the Constitution. FBI check reports no aggravated felony convictions. Docket search reports no pending criminal charges. USCIS interview worksheet reports no false testimony issue.",
      "expected_outcomes": {
        "n400.civics_requirement_satisfied": "true",
        "n400.continuous_residence_satisfied": "true",
        "n400.english_requirement_satisfied": "true",
